# ✅ When You MUST Cancel Requests

| Scenario            | Cancel Needed |
| ------------------- | ------------- |
| Search autocomplete | ✅ YES         |
| Filter dropdowns    | ✅ YES         |
| Infinite scroll     | ✅ YES         |
| Component unmount   | ✅ YES         |
| Page navigation     | ✅ YES         |
| One‑time fetch      | ❌ No          |

***

# ✅ Common Bug This Solves (Very Important)

```txt
User types fast →
Request A (slow) →
Request B (fast) →
A responds after B ❌ (wrong data shown)
```

✅ Cancellation ensures **only latest request wins**

***

# ✅ Interview‑Ready Answer ⭐

> **We cancel previous API requests using `AbortController` in React’s `useEffect` cleanup function to prevent race conditions and stale state updates.**

***

# ✅ One‑Line Answer (Very Common)

**“Use `AbortController` and abort the previous request in `useEffect` cleanup.”**

***

# ✅ Simple Mental Model 🧠

    New effect runs
    ↓
    Old effect cleanup
    ↓
    Abort old request
    ↓
    Fire new request

